en_872154_0	Colonel Anil Perera of the Sri Lanka Sinha Regiment (SLSR) assumed duties as the 9th Commander of the 652 Brigade on 28 Aug during a simple ceremony at the 652 Brigade Headquarters in Anavilandan Kulam, Akkarayankulam.
en_872154_1	A formal Guard Turnout at the entrance, presented by 20 Vijayabahu Infantry Regiment troops greeted him.
en_872154_2	He left his signature in a formal document and symbolized the occasion.
en_872154_3	Afterwards, the newly-appointed Brigade Commander planted a Mango sapling in the compound as a symbol of memory before he joined an all rank tea.
en_872154_4	Commanding Officer of the 7 Sri Lanka National Guard, 20 Vijayabhau Infantry, and Brigade Staff Officers attended the occasion.
